Expanded and accelerated release programs already have begun for recordings by  Leonard Bernstein, one of the most documented conductors in history.
Sony Classical  will begin its three-year release of 75 CDs in January.
Deutsche Grammophon is looking  at his discography.
They had released a CD set in August called "The Bernstein  Edition", which is "selling well."
BGM Classics/RCA Red Seal plans a March re-release  of Bernstein's first commercial recordings from the 1940's.
He had over 200 classical  recordings, but only six videos are available in the home market--three 1971 Beethoven  programs and three movies with scores he composed. 
